{title: When I Get To The End Of The Way}
{artist: Granpa Jones}
{composer: Written by Charles D. Tillman}

[C]The sands have been washed in the [F]footprints
Of the [G7]stranger on Galilee’s [C]shore
And the voice that subdued the rough [F]billows
Will be [G7]heard in Judea no [C]more
But the [G7]path of that lone Gali[C]lean
With [G7]joy I will [D7]follow to[G7]day
And the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way[G7]
And the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way
There are so many hills to climb [F]upward
I [G7]often am longing for [C]rest
But He who appoints me my [F]pathway
Knows [G7]just what is needful and [C]best
I [G7]know in His word He hath [C]promised
That my [G7]strength it shall [D7]be as the [G7]day
And the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way[G7]
And the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way
When the last feeble step has been [F]taken
And the [G7]gates of that city [C]appear
And the beautiful songs of the [F]angels
Float [G7]out on my listening [C]ear
When [G7]all that now seems so [C]mysterious
Will be [G7]bright and as [D7]clear as the [G7]day
And the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way[G7]
Then the [C]toils of the road will seem [F]nothing
When I [G7]get to the end of the [C]way